cat nomefile: concatenate files (or stdin) and prints on stdout
cat nomefile | sort: sort cat nomefile output
cat < nomefile | sort: ridireziona il contenuto di nomefile a cat e invia lo stdout di cat a sort

more nomefile: simple file viewer (1 page at a time->space to scroll)
less nomefile: better file viewer (")

df: report file system disk space usage

touch nomefile: change file timestamps (if no file exists, one is created empty)

ln -s ./old_dir linkdir: make links between files (or directories) (-s: symbolic) (linkdir not yet existing)
hardlink?

alias nomealias='value da sostituire(comando)': definisce (enumera='ls -l') o visualizza (nessun argomento) aliases (shortcut per comandi, comodo)

sort nomefile: write sorted concatenation of file(s) to stdout
sort < nomefile: ridireziona il contenuto di nomefile a sort

ps: report snapshot of current processes of the current userID
riporta PID,TTY(terminal associated with process), TIME (cumulated cpu time), CMD (executable name)
ps -f: process hierarchy (forest)

top: report processes in execution
